Package org.ndnx.ndn.io

Class Summary
GenericObjectInputStream<E> Helper class.
NDNAbstractInputStream This abstract class is the superclass of all classes representing an input stream of bytes segmented and stored in NDN.
NDNAbstractOutputStream This abstract class is the superclass of all classes for writing an output stream of bytes segmented and stored in NDN.
NDNBlockInputStream This input stream expects to do packet-oriented reading of fixed chunks.
NDNBlockOutputStream This class acts as a packet-oriented stream of data.
NDNDescriptor A file descriptor-style wrapper around NDNVersionedInputStream and NDNVersionedOutputStream.
NDNFileInputStream A NDN input stream that expects content names to be versioned, and streams to have a Header containing file-level metadata about each stream.
NDNFileOutputStream A versioned output stream that adds a header containing file-level metadata to every stream it outputs (see Header for contents).
NDNInputStream Perform sequential reads on any segmented NDN content, as if it were a standard InputStream.
NDNOutputStream Basic output stream class which generates segmented content under a given name prefix.
NDNReader Miscellaneous helper functions to read data.
NDNRepositoryWriter A NDNWriter subclass that writes to a repository.
NDNVersionedInputStream A NDNInputStream that reads and writes versioned streams.
NDNVersionedOutputStream An output stream that adds a version to the names it outputs.
NDNWriter Simplest interface to putting data into NDN.
NullOutputStream Helper class -- an interior output stream for a FilterOutputStream where the filter action is the only thing you care about (e.g.
RepositoryFileOutputStream A subclass of NDNFileOutputStream which writes its segments to a repository, using versioned names and writing file-level metadata.
RepositoryOutputStream A subclass of NDNOutputStream which writes its segments to a repository.
RepositoryVersionedOutputStream A subclass of NDNVersionedOutputStream which writes its segments to a repository, using versioned names.
 

Enum Summary
NDNAbstractInputStream.FlagTypes Definitions for flags: DONT_DEREFERENCE: This is used to avoid automatic dereferencing when reading in a link itself BLOCKING: Wait until we see the first segment of the file before we start using timeouts.
NDNDescriptor.OpenMode  
NDNDescriptor.SeekWhence  
 

Exception Summary
ErrorStateException Exception to throw when we are asked to pull data from a network object or stream that is already in an error state.
LinkCycleException Exception to throw when we cannot retrieve data because we have hit a cycle of links.
NoMatchingContentFoundException Exception to throw when a data request times out without returning any matching data.
